  "content": "rgo test -p corvia-kernel chunking_pipeline -- --nocapture`\nExpected: All tests PASS\n\n**Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add crates/corvia-kernel/src/chunking_pipeline.rs\ngit commit -m \"feat(m3.3): wire kernel default strategies into FormatRegistry\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 7: Revise IngestionAdapter Trait (D69)\n\nReplace `ingest() -> Vec<KnowledgeEntry>` with `register_chunking()` + `ingest_sources()`.\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `crates/corvia-kernel/src/traits.rs` (revise trait)\n- Modify: `crates/corvia-kernel/src/chunking_strategy.rs` (ensure SourceFile is pub)\n\n**Step 1: Write the failing test**\n\nAdd a compile-time object-safety test to `traits.rs`:\n\n```rust\n// Compile-time test: verify revised IngestionAdapter is object-safe\nfn _assert_ingestion_adapter_object_safe(_: &dyn IngestionAdapter) {}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Implement the trait revision**\n\nReplace the IngestionAdapter trait in `crates/corvia-kernel/src/traits.rs`:\n\n```rust\n/// Ingestion adapter for domain-specific sources (D11/D69).\n///\n/// D69 clean break: adapters return raw [`SourceFile`]s and register\n/// [`ChunkingStrategy`]s. The kernel's [`ChunkingPipeline`] handles\n/// splitting, merging, and token budget enforcement.\n#[async_trait]\npub trait IngestionAdapter: Send + Sync {\n    /// Domain name (e.g., \"git\", \"general\").\n    fn domain(&self) -> &str;\n\n    /// Register chunking strategies this adapter provides.\n    /// Called once during pipeline setup. The adapter registers",
